<p><b>Fermented food:</b> Fermented foods are a great source of probiotics and arguably one of the best foods to have for gut health. Probiotics improve the gut microbiome and your metabolism. Some probiotics to have in your pantry are kimchi, sauerkraut, yogurt, kefir, tempeh, miso, and kombucha. </p>
				<p><b>Polyphenol-rich foods</b>Foods rich in polyphenols have several health benefits, such as reduction of blood pressure, inflammation, and cholesterol levels. Ensure to consume polyphenol-rich foods like cocoa and chocolate, red wine, almonds, green tea, and blueberries. </p>

<p>Our gut bacteria are essential for maintaining proper health. Whether they are small, like bloating, or significant, like a weak immune system, the bottom is that we can't ignore gut health. A disturbed gut can lead to many problems. A holistic approach is required while restoring gut health. Make sure to eat plenty of fresh fruits, green leafy vegetables, prebiotic and probiotic foods. Make sure to avoid processed food, high sugar foods, reduce stress, and get enough sleep. 
